        <div class="body">
            <p>Of course they are not equal.</p>

<p>You have to keep in mind that languages differ per region.
Brittish english is not american english.</p>

<p>And many bigger sites support both.</p>

<p>So simple as is:
When you support only one english dialect use "en".
But when you also support other dialects then use full locales.</p>

<p>Note:
According to the manual the locale "en_US" is automatically degraded to "en" when "en_US" is not available.
This is no fault, this is expected I18N behaviour and not ZF specific.</p>

